snippet.textDisplay:
Here's my interpretation.
And btw, this is real life I'm talking about.


Nice guy / Good Guy - J and M meet to do the songs.
Had a brief relationship. And probably intense.


Em writes "Normal" from Kamikaze. (It makes sense, since now he sings "don't wanna spend the night acting out 'love the way you lie'". Although he sings "my ex" he's just trying to hide the truth.


Jessie writes on the ORIGINAL version of "imported" (feat JRM)
- Hi my name is (My name is - Eminem)
- doesnt matter (Marshal MATHERS)
and then she goes on to say that M is in love with someone else (his ex, of course) and that if he stays with her (J) she's extra for him, she's too much (makes sense, since he sings "acting out 'love the way you lie'")


Honestly, basicaly all the songs from her album are about them.
Listen to them again "knowing" that they bouth had somtehing and that he ended up with her (because, come on, we all know he loves his ex and always will)


And listen to Farewell (he declairs his love for his ex)
and In Too Deep (again, about his ex where he says "I'm not happy here with her (J)
Rather have you (his ex), rather have me too (back in the days when they bouth got along)"


On the new album, M has a song called "No regrets"...
On the song "Ankles", Jessie says "Apologized, but your Twitter said 'No regrets'"


Guys, keep in mind, they can't bee too explicit! Maybe that's one of the reasons she changed "Imported" lyrics. And also, there's gotta be a "story" behind the song, so some things are made up.


And now you can listen to her songs of this album thinking about that and it will probably makes total sense.




Loved Jessie's album!
